The Tamil Tigers embarked on a tour to garner support for peace talks in Sri Lanka.
A meeting in Switzerland aimed to prepare for negotiations with the government.
Despite ongoing violence and accusations, efforts to resume talks persist.
The government has proposed countermeasures to the rebels' demands.
